track.name: We Never Change
comments: "i wanna live where the sun comes out"
Listening to this song while the snow falls and falls outside here in Chicago..couldnt be happier.
in a wooden house where making more friends would be easy...

I remember buying both A Rush of Blood to the Head and Parachutes when I was twelve, and this song always resonated for me... amazing what odd memories it brings back, although I feel like I understand this song eight years later far more than I did back then.
Where is the Coldplay of those years?
I want to live life, and always be true, and I want to live life, and be good to you, and I want to fly, and never come down, and live my life, and have friends around.
i wanna live in a wooden house. i wanna live life and always be true. i wanna live life and be good to you.
